+## Phase 14A output summary
+
+Phase 14A defines Mobile & Rapid Capture architecture boundaries before runtime mobile/offline expansion. The review confirms current staff-scoped, organization-scoped operational workflows and intelligence-awareness layers remain authoritative and read-only where expected, identifies rapid-capture friction points across attendance/notes/tasks/events/FieldOps/review workflows, separates mobile optimization from offline runtime and messaging/feed/automation concerns, documents core mobile/capture risks, establishes a strict “Do Not Implement Yet” scope, recommends a safe first mobile web capture slice, and provides a blocking checklist that must be completed before offline/mobile runtime work.
+
+## PR Summary
+
+This phase delivers documentation-only Mobile & Rapid Capture architecture boundaries for CadreOS. It reviews Arc 8–13 operational and awareness outputs, maps current capture friction across attendance, notes, tasks, events, operational review, and FieldOps workflows, and defines strict boundary separations (mobile vs offline, rapid capture vs Feed/Inbox, awareness vs messaging, acceleration vs automation). It records mobile/capture risk areas, adds a “Do Not Implement Yet” section, recommends a safe first staff-only mobile web capture slice, and adds a blocking checklist before any offline/mobile runtime implementation. No runtime behavior was introduced.
